# Deploy Simulator — Project Context

CI/CD deployment simulator. Read this before making changes.

## Directory layout

- `App/` — all application code (models, logic, API, CLI, tests co-located under App as the project grows)
- Root — `README.md`, `.gitignore`, `requirements.txt` only (no app modules at repo root)

## Stack

- Python 3
- Pydantic v2 (`BaseModel`, `Field`, `typing.Literal`) for data validation

## Operations

`App/deployment_ops.py` defines `DeploymentOps` with a `Queue[Deployment]` store:

- `add_deployment` — enqueue a running deployment (duration must be 0)
- `complete_deployment(deployment_id, status, timestamp)` — finalize a running deployment; duration is computed from timestamps
- `read_deployments` (optional service/status filters), `read_deployment` (by id), `read_running_deployments`, `read_latest_completed_deployments`

`App/metric.py` defines `MetricOps` for analytics over completed deployments:

- `record_completed(deployment)` — per-service stats, status counts, anomaly detection
- `read_anomalies`, `success_rate`, `p95_duration`

`App/dummy_generator.py` defines `DummyGenerator`:

- `create_dummy_deployment()` returns a running deployment dict; generator completes deployments after a simulated duration

`App/main.py` — FastAPI app with session-scoped `DeploymentOps` and `DummyGenerator` (lifespan startup):

- `GET /deployments`, `GET /deployments/latest`, `GET /deployments/running`, `GET /deployments/{id}`, `PATCH /deployments/{id}`, `POST /deployments/start`, `POST /deployments/stop`
- Structured error responses for 404, 422, 409, 500

`DeploymentOps.add_deployment` rejects duplicate ids and maintains `id → Deployment` index.

## Data model

`App/models.py` defines `Deployment`:

- `id` — int, >= 1
- `service` — one of: `billing-api`, `auth-service`, `notifications`, `frontend-web`
- `status` — one of: `running`, `success`, `fail`, `rolled-back` (`running` is in-flight; duration is 0 until completion)
- `duration` — float, seconds, >= 0
- `timestamp` — str (ISO 8601)
- `commit_sha` — str, 7–40 characters

## Conventions

- New application modules go under `App/`, not the repo root
- Match existing style: type aliases for `Literal` unions, Pydantic `Field` descriptions
- Keep changes focused; do not expand scope unless asked
